    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 431.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 418 of the 27th
                    ultimo, I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy of a note which I have
                    received from the Marquis of Lansdowne in relation to the American prisoners of
                    war in Ceylon, together with a copy of a telegram<note n="a" xml:id="d456fna"
                        >Printed, ante.</note> which I sent you on the 21st instant, from which it
                    will be observed that the American consul at Colombo can communicate with the 22
                    prisoners of war, but that all communications should be made either through the
                    governor of Ceylon or through the general officer commanding the troops.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph H. Choate.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0548" n="468" xml:id="pg_468"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Lansdowne</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Choate</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-17">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Your Excellency</hi>: The Marquis of Salisbury referred
                        your letter of the 25th ultimo to the secretary of state for war, and I have
                        now the honor to inform your excellency that a telegram has been received
                        from the military authorities in Ceylon to the effect that there is no
                        objection to the United States consul at Colombo communicating with the 22
                        prisoners of war referred to in your excellency’s note, but that all
                        communications should be made either through the governor of Ceylon or
                        through the general officer commanding the troops.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansdowne</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
